    <td><div align="center"><b><font size=-1>Map of &quot;Virginia&quot;, home of the Wiroans, by Captain John
  White (1585).&nbsp; White's map shows only a portion of  the extensive land allocated to the original Virginia Colony.&nbsp; Ironically, the map does not include any of modern day Virginia (the border of which is located just beyond the top of the map).&nbsp; The coastline seen here is largely that of modern day North Carolina.&nbsp; Note the fine representation of the Outer Banks.&nbsp; The lower left depicts the northernmost region of what is now South Carolina. </font></b>
